{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-programs-js","path":"/programs/response-target-indicators.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<style>\n.contents {\n  margin-left: 1.45rem;\n  margin-right: 1.45rem;\n  border-radius: 0.3em;\n  width: 60%;\n}\n</style>\n<p>HackerOne utilizes average metrics and colored indicators to show how your program is doing in meeting healthy success criteria.</p>\n<h3 id=\"average-response-efficiency-metrics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#average-response-efficiency-metrics\" aria-label=\"average response efficiency metrics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Average Response Efficiency Metrics</h3>\n<p>HackerOne displays a program's average response efficiency metrics on the security page to enable hackers to see how responsive your program is in:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>giving a first response</li>\n<li>paying out a bounty</li>\n<li>resolving a vulnerability</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The average times are calculated on a rolling 3 month basis, and you can configure which metrics to display in <strong>Program Settings > Program > Metrics Display</strong>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 496px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 151.99999999999997%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"response-sla-indicator-1\"\n        title=\"response-sla-indicator-1\"\n        src=\"/static/356b61eaa4b74b277076a9c0a9d1d901/bb630/response-indicators-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/356b61eaa4b74b277076a9c0a9d1d901/fac75/response-indicators-1.png 125w,\n/static/356b61eaa4b74b277076a9c0a9d1d901/63868/response-indicators-1.png 250w,\n/static/356b61eaa4b74b277076a9c0a9d1d901/bb630/response-indicators-1.png 496w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 496px) 100vw, 496px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"colored-indicators\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#colored-indicators\" aria-label=\"colored indicators permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Colored Indicators</h3>\n<p>A program’s performance against HackerOne's response standards (Time to First Response = 5 business days; Time to Triage = 10 business days) is displayed on its security page and report submission page. This provides additional context to potential hackers when they're looking to submit reports to your program.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 461px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 40.8%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"response-sla-indicator-2\"\n        title=\"response-sla-indicator-2\"\n        src=\"/static/92ff7df49b2152cfbe4d72041f599346/f816d/response-indicator-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/92ff7df49b2152cfbe4d72041f599346/fac75/response-indicator-2.png 125w,\n/static/92ff7df49b2152cfbe4d72041f599346/63868/response-indicator-2.png 250w,\n/static/92ff7df49b2152cfbe4d72041f599346/f816d/response-indicator-2.png 461w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 461px) 100vw, 461px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h4 id=\"indicator-details\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#indicator-details\" aria-label=\"indicator details permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Indicator Details</h4>\n<p>How are the percentages calculated? </p>\n<ul>\n<li>The percentage is determined by this calculation: <strong>((1-(# of reports that didn't meet response standards / # of total reports created))* 100)</strong></li>\n<li>The percentage of reports that meet response standards is based on reports created within the last 90 days. </li>\n<li>If a report violated response standards at some point during the last 90 days but is no longer violating the standards, it'll still count towards the # of reports that didn't meet response standards.</li>\n<li>A single report can violate both the response standards for Time to First Response and Time to Triage but each report can only count once as a report that didn't meet the response standards. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>A colored indicator accompanies the percentage of reports that meet response standards. Below are the indicator types and criteria:</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Indicator Type</th>\n<th>Criteria</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Green</td>\n<td>≥ 75% of reports meet response standards</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Yellow</td>\n<td>&#x3C; 75% and ≥ 25% of reports meet response standards</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Red</td>\n<td>&#x3C; 25% of reports meet response standards</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","frontmatter":{"path":"/programs/response-target-indicators.html","id":"programs/response-target-indicators","title":"Response Target Indicators","description":null},"headings":[{"value":"Average Response Efficiency Metrics"},{"value":"Colored Indicators"}]}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}